$ Git option: http.proxySSLCAInfo
@ http.proxySSLCAInfo

Name of the file (for example `→ Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Git[C:\Program Files\Git]\mingw64\ssl\certs\ca-bundle.crt`) that contains the → development/security/cryptography/public-key/certificate[certificate]
with which a peer is verified in → development/version-control-systems/git/commands/pull[`git pull`] or → development/version-control-systems/git/commands/push[`git push`] over → development/web/HTTPS.

sa:

  The error message *unable to access 'https://github.com/…': error setting certificate verify locations:  CAfile: …*.

  Other → development/version-control-systems/git/options[Git options]
